  "data": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<div class=\"spell-description\">\n  <p>\n    <strong>School</strong>&nbsp;enchantment&nbsp;(charm)&nbsp;[mind-affecting];\n    <strong>Level</strong>&nbsp;bard 4, mesmerist 4, occultist 4, psychic 5, shaman 5, sorcerer/wizard 5, witch 5;\n    \n    \n    \n    \n  </p>\n  <p>\n    <strong>Casting Time</strong>&nbsp;1 standard action<br>\n    <strong>Components</strong>&nbsp;V, S<br>\n  </p>\n  <p>\n    <strong>Range</strong>&nbsp;close (25 ft. + 5 ft./2 levels)<br>\n    \n    <strong>Targets</strong>&nbsp;one or more humanoid creatures, no two of which can be more than 30 ft. apart<br>\n    \n    <strong>Duration</strong>&nbsp;1 hour/level<br>\n    <strong>Saving Throw</strong>&nbsp;Will negates;&nbsp;<strong>Spell Resistance</strong>&nbsp;yes<br>\n  </p>\n  <h2>Description</h2>\n  <p>This spell functions like <i>charm person</i>, except that mass <i>charm person</i> affects a number of humanoid creatures whose combined Hit Dice don't exceed twice your level. If there are more potential targets than you can affect, you choose them one at a time until you reach the limit of HD you can affect. If you cast mass <i>charm person</i> on only one creature, you ignore the spell's HD limit.</p>\n</div>\n",
